timing_disable...uential_checks(25.10)  timing_disable...uential_checks(25.10)

Name
       timing_disable_non_sequential_checks

Syntax
       timing_disable_non_sequential_checks

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       When set to true, disables the timing arcs between any data-to-clock or
       clock-to-clock  checks  which have a timing_type attribute equal to one
       of the following:

              * non_seq_setup_rising

              * non_seq_setup_falling

              * non_seq_hold_rising

              * non_seq_hold_falling

       This global only affects non-sequential checks where the reference  pin
       of  the  timing  check  is a clock pin. Data-to-data checks - where the
       reference pin of the timing check is a data pin - are not  affected  by
       this  global.  To  disable  data-to-data  checks  you must use the tim-
       ing_disable_library_data_to_data_checks global.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

